last_episode_to_air.name: Bring It Live! Detour
last_episode_to_air.overview: The Dancing Dolls hit the road, but obstacles along the way leave the fate of the tour in jeopardy; Princess battles overcoming her fears; Kayla tries to find her voice through dance; Faith struggles to find confidence on the floor after an injury.

name: Bring It!
overview: A spotlight on the elite world of hip-hop majorette competitions. Coach Dianna Williams (aka "Miss D") and her Dancing Dolls troupe refuse to lose, pushing themselves to the limit each week in the relentless pursuit of victory. Every pump, thrust and high kick on "Bring It!" highlights the triumphs and struggles of intense competition, where errors aren't tolerated, mediocrity isn’t excused and only a win is acceptable.
tagline: It’s a doll’s world. Until now.

episodes.name: You Better Bring It!
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls dance team prepares to compete against a fierce rival in Chattanooga, TN. Head coach, Dianna, forbids a number of dancers from participating at the event after less-than-perfect performances at rehearsal and team captain, Kayla, struggles with the added pressure of performing a solo. Meanwhile, Rittany, one of the dancers' moms, butts heads with Dianna and threatens to pull her daughter from the team.

episodes.name: Battle in Memphis
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls compete in Memphis against some of the best dance teams in the South. Rittany tires of Dianna's harsh teaching style and pulls Crystianna out of rehearsal; and a judging controversy leads to a riot.

episodes.name: The Wig Is Off
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls return to Memphis hoping to beat one of their biggest rivals.

episodes.name: "Baby" Doll Don't Mean "Baby"
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls get their pint-sized counterparts, the Baby Dancing Dolls, to compete in their place so they can focus on developing a secret weapon to defeat their biggest rival, the Prancing Tigerettes.

episodes.name: Sunjai in Stilettos
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls travel to Memphis to compete against two fierce rivals.

episodes.name: Street Battle
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls challenge their rivals to a street battle; tension on the dance floor sparks a clash between dancers and spectators.

episodes.name: Shut Up and Dance
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls prepare to defend their title against local rivals, as Mimi tries to convince Dianna to let the mothers back into the dance studio during rehearsal.

episodes.name: The Lock-In
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls struggle to master difficult stands and they prepare for a competition in Memphis.

episodes.name: The Finale: Battle Royale
episodes.overview: Season 1 ends with the Dancing Dolls competing in a winner-take-all "Battle Royale." The dancers feel extra pressure to perform well when they learn that the judges are professional dancers and choreographers who may be looking to discover someone.

episodes.name: Miss D Breaks It Down
episodes.overview: Dianna shares secrets from Season 1 and offers a history of the hip-hop majorettes.

episodes.name: Best of the Battles
episodes.overview: The most memorable performances and defining moments from Season 1 are featured.

episodes.name: So You Wanna Be A Doll?
episodes.overview: In season 1.5, Miss D holds tryouts for veteran dolls and new hopefuls.

episodes.name: Prom or Competition?
episodes.overview: With the Bay Area Battle looming, Miss D prepares the new members and stand battle squad for the competition.

episodes.name: A New Rival Emerges
episodes.overview: A new cocky team from Miami, Florida challenges the Dancing Dolls to a stand battle.

episodes.name: Kayla's Big Surprise
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls step outside their comfort zone and perform a lyrical dance routine.

episodes.name: Nashville Smackdown
episodes.overview: The team travels to Nashville to battle their one of their biggest rivals, Ladies of Excellence.

episodes.name: Baby Dolls vs. Baby Tigerettes
episodes.overview: The moms and the Baby Dancing Dolls get the spotlight when the moms perform in creative dance with Kayla, Sunjai, and Camryn's dads, but Crystianna's aunt, Rittany, can't keep up with the choreography.

episodes.name: Pray for Sunjai
episodes.overview: When Sunjai struggles to make the stand battle squad, it sends Miss D's nerves in a spiral, prompting Kayla to come to the rescue.

episodes.name: Dolls vs. Dollz: The Rematch
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls and the Dynamic Diamond Dollz go at it once more to settle some unfinished business.

episodes.name: Bucking for Revenge
episodes.overview: The Dolls go back to Memphis to face the Dynamic Diamond Dollz after having to settle for a tie the week before, but first, they must contend with a wide range of competitors and the Baby Dancing Dolls are featured in the parade category.

episodes.name: Chumps or Champions?
episodes.overview: The competition season concludes with one final championship event.

episodes.name: The DD4L Tour
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls go on the road to different cities on a "Buck or Die" camp to teach children majorette dance styles.

episodes.name: Specials Inside the Dollhouse: Your Questions Answered
Miami Heat is Back
episodes.overview: It's a brand new competition season and Miss D is determined to whip the Dancing Dolls into an unstoppable dance machine! Talented new rival, the YCDT Supastarz of Miami, FL, return to Jackson to prove their victory over the Dolls last season was more than just beginner's luck and Dianna creates an elaborate routine designed to mock their coach, Tracy. Meanwhile, new Dancing Doll parent, Tawantza, wastes no time before butting heads with Coach D after her daughter, Zatia, gets cut.

episodes.name: Miss D Loses Her Cool
episodes.overview: Tensions run high as the Dancing Dolls go head-to-head with archrival, the Divas of Olive Branch.

episodes.name: Hometown Showdown
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls battle it out against the Purple Diamonds. Dianna has a surprising secret weapon.

episodes.name: Bucking in Bama
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls head deep into uncharted territory when they attend a competition in Mobile, Alabama. Camryn takes the reins as Head Captain for the week and struggles as she attempts to lead stand battle for the very first time. Meanwhile, Rittany considers taking her niece to join a rival dance squad after she and Dianna clash over Crystianna cheerleading.

episodes.name: Selena's Triple Threat
episodes.overview: The girls prepare for a battle in New Orleans; a trash-talking rival re-emerges; Selena's twin daughters make cuts.

episodes.name: No Stopping Kayla
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls head deep into enemy territory to challenge Mobile, Alabama's number one dance squad, the Diamondettes, on their own home turf. Meanwhile, Miss D confronts Kayla about her recent weight gain as she prepares for a high stakes solo performance and Star, Sky and ZaTia try their best to crush it in t

episodes.name: Stamp Out Atlanta
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls must take home a first place trophy or risk losing their reputation; Camryn struggles after Miss D taps her to represent the team in the solo category; Tawantza pressures her daughter ZaTia to step up her game.

episodes.name: Traci's Revenge
episodes.overview: Coach Traci and the YCDT Supastarz return to Mississippi looking for revenge after losing to Dianna and the Dolls the last time they battled

episodes.name: Captain Down
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls travel back to Atlanta for a rematch against the Dazzling Divas; Selena butts heads with Miss D after Sunjai fails to make cuts in creative dance; an injury threatens to keep Kayla from performing.

episodes.name: Don't Do It Neva
episodes.overview: The beef between the Dancing Dolls and the Divas of Olive Branch reaches a whole new level when Miss D and Coach Neva decide to join their squads on the dance floor.

episodes.name: Baby Tiger Attack
episodes.overview: As the Baby Dancing Dolls attempt to defeat their biggest rival, the Baby Prancing Tigerettes, for the first time ever, Tigerette coach Quincy causes a stir when he reveals some controversial choreography. Meanwhile, Tina and Mimi butt heads with the Baby Dancing Doll Moms and Tawantza secretly tries to play the conflict to her advantage by positioning herself as a mentor to the next generation of Dancing Doll Parents.

episodes.name: Copycat
episodes.overview: Coming off a surprising loss to Coach Quincy and the Baby Prancing Tigerettes in the Battle of the Babies, Miss D is out for retribution this week when the Big Dolls go head-to-head with the Tigerettes.

episodes.name: Road to Royale
episodes.overview: Miss D and the Dancing Dolls finally get a chance to go toe-to-toe with their crosstown rival the Purple Diamonds after losing to them at the beginning of the season.

episodes.name: Battle Royale 2015
episodes.overview: Miss D and the Dancing Dolls face off against their three biggest rivals, Purple Diamonds, YCDT Supastarz of Miami and the Divas of Olive Branch, in the final and most anticipated competition of the season, the Battle Royale.

episodes.name: Rival Rehash
episodes.overview: In this special episode of "Bring It!," exclusive uncut stand battles from this year’s Battle Royale, as well as a special extended version of this past season’s most explosive face-off with the Dolls’ arch nemesis, the Divas of Olive Branch, help provide a new perspective on the Dancing Dolls’ fiercest rivalries.

episodes.name: A Whole New Doll Game
episodes.overview: The summer season is here and things are heating up in the Dollhouse! Miss Dianna is shaking things up in the studio, throwing the team and the Dancing Doll Parents into frenzy.

episodes.name: Dancing Dolls NOT for Life
episodes.overview: The heat of the summer season reaches a boiling point when Tawantza's temper flares out-of-control.

episodes.name: Selena's Makeover Madness
episodes.overview: Everything is on the line this week as Dianna decides to take a risk and put new dancers on the front lines against returning rival team, Infamous Dancerettes, who have been sharpening their skills and are ready to take on the Dolls.

episodes.name: The Big Apple and the Bitter Apple
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls are up against a heated rival this week, none other than Quincy and his Prancing Tigerettes.

episodes.name: Saturday Night Fights
episodes.overview: Coach D takes the Dancing Dolls out of their comfort zone and onto a football field for a spectacular Saturday Night Lights field show and stand battle competition.

episodes.name: Who You Callin' Cookie
episodes.overview: New teams are traveling far and wide to take on the Dancing Dolls and Miss D is feeling the pressure.

episodes.name: Pom Pom Panic
episodes.overview: Pom-poms are flying this week as Dianna coaches the girls through a Southern stand-off.

episodes.name: Tick, Tick, Boom!
episodes.overview: With the Summer Slam Dance Championship only week away, the girls feel extra pressure to show off their talents and prove to Miss D that they have what it takes to be captain of the team next season.

episodes.name: Summer Slam
episodes.overview: Season Finale

episodes.name: Straight Outta Jackson
episodes.overview: Coach D is determined to lead her Dolls to victory in this week's street battle against Compton.

episodes.name: The Bucking Ballerina
episodes.overview: Dianna struggles to get her new team into shape; Crystianna and Faith vie for a solo; Dana makes waves in the viewing room; Dana wants to give the mothers makeovers.

episodes.name: Hell Week
episodes.overview: Coach D has a show-stopping idea, but the Dolls' participation is put at risk; and Dianna is forced to change her choreography at the last minute. Elsewhere, the Dancing Doll parents are near their wits' end after a new mom arrives.

episodes.name: Homecoming Hell
episodes.overview: Dianna and the Dolls are busy preparing for a competition, homecoming parade and halftime show; and the DDPs and Baby Dolls participate in the team's field show. Later, Dianna throws a stand at the Divas of Olive Branch.

episodes.name: Rittany's Revolt
episodes.overview: Rittany throws a wrench in Dianna's plan after hearing the team's participating in another parade. Later, Dianna forces Rittany to make a tough decision regarding Crystianna's participation in the parade and this week's competition.

episodes.name: The Wicked Witch of Jackson
episodes.overview: It's `Fright Night in the Dollhouse' and Dianna has big plans for a show-stopping Halloween routine, but deadly rivals The Purple Diamonds have other ideas.

episodes.name: Bucking Bride
episodes.overview: Dianna prepares an ambitious gospel duet with an unlikely pair; Tina prepares for her wedding; Selena finds out she has not been invited to Tina's wedding.

episodes.name: Blow It Up
episodes.overview: The Dolls rehearse for a pom-pom competition against their Texas rivals, Xplosive, and the new girls struggle to catch on. Meanwhile, Dianna cuts the Battle Royale soloist hopefuls down to six dancers; and Selena confronts Miss D about Sky's chances.

episodes.name: Flash Mob Madness
episodes.overview: Dianna asks Kayla to help choreograph a hip-hop routine, but her controlling ways prevent Kayla from leading the team. Later, the parents get in an argument after Rittany blames the team's losing streak on Faith.

episodes.name: 3 Strikes, You're Out
episodes.overview: Dianna choreographs a '90s-inspired, TLC-themed dance; Dianna struggles to get the team in shape.

episodes.name: Neva Gets Even
episodes.overview: Neva crosses the line in Stand Battle this week; state testing forces Miss D to make a risky decision; Tina goes on the offensive when a new coach threatens to sideline Kayla.

episodes.name: They're Coming for Us!!
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls must take on eight of their fiercest rivals to secure a spot in the Battle Royale; Camryn is pushed to her limits; Mimi is fired up over the new mothers' lack of support for their captain.

episodes.name: Face the Music! It's the Finale!
episodes.overview: After losing the Battle Royale two years in a row, Dianna overloads her team with complicated choreography and ambitious stands that involve guest appearances from alumni.

episodes.name: Spilling the Tea Reunion Special
episodes.overview: Things get `real real' when Vivica Fox hosts a full cast reunion.

episodes.name: Team Kayla vs. Team Dianna
episodes.overview: For the first time in Dollhouse history, Coach D splits the Dancing Dolls into two teams for a fiercely competitive scrimmage match

episodes.name: The Return of Neva the Diva
episodes.overview: Coach D enlists the Dancing Dolls in a grudge match with her most bitter rival, Neva-the-Diva. Dianna will stop at nothing to beat her arch-nemesis.

episodes.name: Compton Call Out
episodes.overview: Coach D accepts a rematch from the Divas of Compton; one of the parents loses control when Coach D decides to shake things up; Mimi struggles to let Camryn begin dating.

episodes.name: Ratchcity
episodes.overview: After a series of losses in the freestyle category, Coach D decides to whip her team into shape.

episodes.name: Hoop Dreams Drama
episodes.overview: Coach D is 'ballin' in the Dollhouse this week, as she takes her game to the next level and enlists her husband to help with an ambitious basketball-themed routine.

episodes.name: Scholarship Dreams and Dating Nightmares
episodes.overview: The dancers compete for a scholarship at a local university; Coach D must train the battle squad to dance on a college level.

episodes.name: Dancing With the Enemy
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls team up with their rivals, the Purple Diamonds, to take on Memphis in a city vs. city competition; Coach D choreographs an ambitious creative dance; Sunjai gives Camryn a tour of her college campus.

episodes.name: Wigging Out
episodes.overview: Coach D's plans backfire when her decision to include 30 new dancers in a football field competition puts the team in jeopardy for game day.

episodes.name: Lil Niqo and a LOT of Sweat!
episodes.overview: During the week of the final competition before the Summer Dance Slam, Coach D turns up the heat.

episodes.name: Stomp! Summer Slam Shocker
episodes.overview: Coach D choreographs a stepping routine for the Summer Dance Slam.

episodes.name: Miss D Reboots
episodes.overview: Bring It!’s back for a brand new season and for their first competition, Coach D goes up against her arch rival Neva the Diva in a New Orleans dance battle. This week the battle squad gets some fresh blood and the DDP welcome a brand new member to the Viewing Room, the outspoken and outrageous Brandon, uncle to twins Angel and Angela.

episodes.name: Dianna Said Knock You Out!
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls are stepping into the ring with a boxing-themed routine against unknown rivals Black Ice, and find their opponents really pack a punch. Meanwhile, Selena goes for her first ride-along to become a full-fledged bounty hunter and Kayla trains Camryn, Crystianna, and Makyla for their first ever 3-way Captain’s Battle.

episodes.name: Coach D Meets Queen B
episodes.overview: Coach D needs her Dancing Dolls to slay the competition after the results from the last competition. With a crash course in “New Orleans bounce,” can the dolls bounce back? Also some of the girls get an amazing opportunity to see Beyoncé in concert and the DDPs get a rare night out that’s a real drag!

episodes.name: Bringing It to the Big Apple
episodes.overview: Coach D has a big surprise for the Dolls–twelve girls have been selected to go on a field trip to New York City! But this is no sightseeing vacation–the...

episodes.name: Torrey Takes Over
episodes.overview: Dianna unexpectedly hires a new ballet coach, leading Tina to believe the new guy will replace Kayla. Later, Kayla searches for a studio to teach hip-hop classes; and the dancers struggle to master new lyrical skills in time for a freestyle competition.

episodes.name: Losing Faith
episodes.overview: The Dolls perform with props; and Faith and Daija are assigned a ballet routine taught by Torrey. Later, Faith feels like she's missing out on a normal teenage life due to her busy schedule.

episodes.name: A Tale of Two Dollhouses
episodes.overview: Dianna travels to Birmingham to prep her new dancers for a scrimmage against the Jackson, Miss., team. Later, Kayla rises to the challenge at home; and Torrey takes matters into his own hands at the Jackson studio.

episodes.name: Attack of the B Squad
episodes.overview: Coach D adds a twist to a stand battle. Later, the Doll veterans are temporarily benched as a new B squad is thrown into battle; and tensions rise as one of Brandon's twins makes cuts, which leads Brandon to confront Miss D.

episodes.name: Black Ice Meltdown
episodes.overview: Black Ice is back and Miss D is bringing the heat. Meanwhile, Crystianna and Makylah find themselves tested when they have to choreograph a routine for a co-captain's battle; and Rittany throws herself a roaring '20s-themed birthday bash that's chock full of surprises.

episodes.name: Revenge of the Robo-Dolls
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls go up against arch rivals the Prancing Tigerettes. Later, Coach D bites off more than she can chew with a futuristic robot-creative routine and a new category called tag team.

episodes.name: Cookie Bites Back
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls find out that Coach D swapped studios with Tyrus, the flamboyant coach of the Elite Stars. Later, he decides to bench Coach D's pros and take a chance on new blood.

episodes.name: La La Land
episodes.overview: The Dolls take on Los Angeles for a grudge match against Compton; and one doll gets the opportunity of a lifetime, while the team learn Coach D's Smurf creative. Later, Demi Lovato surprises the girls.

episodes.name: Lemons to "Lemonade?"
episodes.overview: When the Dancing Dolls are going up against their hometown rivals, the Purple Diamonds, Coach D makes a Beyoncé-inspired routine that will have the girls performing in a pool; Kayla second guesses her future after a bad audition in Los Angeles.

episodes.name: Battle for Broadway
episodes.overview: The Broadway Dance Center comes to Jackson to pick one doll for their summer-intensive scholarship. Later, Kayla reinvigorates her passion for dance by taking the girls that aren't auditioning to perform in a no-rules, freestyle hip-hop competition.

episodes.name: Deliver Us From Neva
episodes.overview: With Battle Royale looming, Coach D holds tryouts for a solo role that Rittany's gunning for Crystianna to get. Later, Coach D makes cuts to put together a battle squad, but first the Dolls must get through a battle against two of their biggest nemeses, Sharon and the Southern Royalettes and Neva and her Divas of Olive Branch.

episodes.name: Battle Royale: Up in Flames!
episodes.overview: It’s the Battle Royale, and Dianna’s concocted her most ambitious creative dance yet, a spectacular Willy Wonka-inspired routine. Meanwhile, Kayla struggles with her dance career outside the Dollhouse and Rittany reaches a breaking point. Throw in Black Ice, the Prancing Tigerettes and unexpected fire — will the Dolls reign victorious or will everything go up in flames?!

episodes.name: Crossing The Line
episodes.overview: As a brand new dance season begins, Coach D has decided to shake-up EVERYTHING familiar in the Dollhouse. The DDPs get a rude awakening when they find out their antics have them permanently exiled from the viewing room. Meanwhile, new faces are causing a commotion in the Dollhouse and Chrystianna stirring-up trouble in enemy territory.

episodes.name: Rumble in the Jungle
episodes.overview: When a Dollhouse heavy-hitter gets injured, a new DDP tries to sweet talk her way up the Dollhouse ladder. Rittany questions her decision to defect from the team. Also, when Dianna puts the heat on her new Baby Doll team, a Baby Mama mutiny erupts.

episodes.name: #Clapback
episodes.overview: After defecting to Divas of Olive Branch, a regretful Rittany tries to woo Coach D into letting Crystianna back on the team. Will Dianna take her co-captain back or will she exile Rittany for good? Meanwhile, the Dancing Dolls prepare for an epic stand battle against Neva-the-Diva, and both teams are pulling out ALL the "punches".

episodes.name: Battle for Oz
episodes.overview: Broadway singer and international star, Todrick Hall, surprises the Dolls with a "Oz" inspired choreography challenge that pits Dolls against Dolls. When the competition heats up, tears are shed, and tempers flare in effort to win the performance opportunity of a lifetime.

episodes.name: Secrets Lies and Slumber parties
episodes.overview: Dianna announces she will be taking only five Dancing Dolls to a national competition at the end of the season; Rittany and Dana plan to throw a slumber party that seconds as a dancing workshop, but not everyone is on the invite list.

episodes.name: Coach D Resigns
episodes.overview: oach D's frustration with the Dancing Dolls' lackluster attitudes results in her dramatic departure from the Dollhouse days before a major competition; Rittany decides to pursue an unconventional way to start a family.

episodes.name: Stand Battle Shake Up
episodes.overview: Dianna announces the mothers will be a mandatory part of Stand Battle, but only those who display the best "bucking" and "booty shaking" will survive the cut; jealousy ensues after some of the parents are rejected.

episodes.name: Dolls Meets World
episodes.overview: nna takes a big risk by placing untried girls at the forefront of an elaborate "around-the-world" creative routine; a reluctant Rittany goes on a blind date; Kayla is persuaded to visit Grambling State University for a 48-hour stay.

episodes.name: The Dolls' Last Chance
episodes.overview: Coach D enlists celebrity choreographers to train, audition and select five girls for the national competition. Kayla's coaching dreams are on the line as she scrambles to prepare her newly formed dance team for their first hip-hop competition.

episodes.name: National Pressure
episodes.overview: After months of intense training, Coach D and the Dancing Dolls head to Philadelphia for an epic competition with a multitude of dance genres; the pressure intensifies when the group learns they are the only team dancing majorette at the competition.

episodes.name: National Pressure
episodes.overview: After months of intense training, Coach D and the Dancing Dolls head to Philadelphia for an epic competition with a multitude of dance genres; the pressure intensifies when the group learns they are the only team dancing majorette at the competition.

episodes.name: If You Can't Stand the Heat...
episodes.overview: In the Season 5 opener, Coach D tries to find the Dancing Dolls' next captain. Also, a new dancer and DDP shakes up the team after moving from New York City to Jackson and introducing some high-maintenance demands.

episodes.name: The Sister Showdown
episodes.overview: The Dollhouse takes "sibling rivalry" to the next level when the dollhouse "captain nominee" must stand off against her sister, who just happens to be the captain of Jackson's hometown enemy, the Purple Diamonds. Meanwhile, Selena deals with a "twin dilemma" when she tries to make one twin follow her sister's path.

episodes.name: Let's Talk About Texts, Baby
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls prepare for a big school-spirit competition, but the practices get interrupted when a texting scandal rocks the team.

episodes.name: Rivals united for a cause
episodes.overview: Coach D organizes a show-stopping competition to raise money for dance teams who lost their studios in Hurricane Harvey. It's a full house as all of coach D's rivals, both friends and foes, battle it out in competition for a cause. Meanwhile, tensions rise between two new DDP who can't seem to put aside their differences.

episodes.name: B-Squad Goals
episodes.overview: Coach D puts the B-Squad on the front line for Stand Battle; the DDP consult a psychic who has an unsettling prediction about future Dollhouse shake-ups.

episodes.name: Banned 4 Life
episodes.overview: The three suspended potential captains must earn their way back into Coach D's good graces.

episodes.name: Stands and Deliver
episodes.overview: The Dolls face off against the Prancing Tigerettes and Divas of Olive Branch in a heated Stands in Stands battle with a live band.

episodes.name: Dance For Your Rights
episodes.overview: Coach D creates a female empowerment routine that she believes will rock the dance floor. But when she gets carried away, her routine quickly spirals into a 28-minute dance marathon that exhausts the team and her lead Dancing Doll. Will the dancers overcome fatigue and confusion on the floor, or will the routine crash and burn? Meanwhile, a few paranoid DDPs suspect Jaylene is being secretly groomed for the captain position and investigate.

episodes.name: Who Wants to Be a Prop Star?
episodes.overview: The Dolls prepare for a special Stand Battle that includes props, but Coach D fears the routine will fail when the dancers struggle to catch on to the choreography. Former DDP Rittany returns as her sister, Valisa, lashes out at Coach D's decisions.

episodes.name: Grudge Match Gone Wrong
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls face off against their most formidable foe, Black Ice, in an epic grudge match, but when the team's secret weapon backfires, the Dolls are left without a plan of attack. An emergency situation sends the competition into chaos.

episodes.name: Three's a Crowd
episodes.overview: Dianna travels to the Birmingham Dollhouse to coach the Baby Dolls for their first big competition and finds complete chaos. Dianna leaves Kayla in charge to coach the Jackson Dolls and help her narrow down the final picks for the captain's position.

episodes.name: The Ultimate Captain's Battle
episodes.overview: Coach D narrows the search for the new captain to the final two and challenges them to face off in a heated Doll vs. Doll competition. Emotions explode and tears flow when Coach D lashes out at both potential captains for not leading their teams.

episodes.name: Clash of the Titans
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls launch a fierce agenda to win the seniors’ final Battle Royale. Coach D choreographs an epic Egyptian creative, complete with mummy baby dolls, giant phoenixes, and even an untamed wild animal. Dianna and guest judge, Laurieann Gibson, get into a major brawl. Plus, Coach D decides once and for all who will be the next captain of the Dancing Dolls.

episodes.name: No Boys Allowed?
episodes.overview: Major changes hit the Dollhouse as Camryn steps down as captain. Coach D breaks her biggest rule, shaking the Dollhouse to its core. The wild experiment led by Coach D's new permanent assistant coach, Marquell, sends the team into complete chaos.

episodes.name: A Dollhouse Abandoned
episodes.overview: The Dolls go down like dominos as they prepare for their first stand battle of the season with both boys and girls competing. Coach D and Marquell must make some tough cuts, as not all the new members are ready. But when a betrayal like no other rattles the Dollhouse, emotions run high and the team is faced with their toughest decision yet: to battle or forfeit the competition.

episodes.name: So You Think You Can Choreograph?
episodes.overview: It's a senior showdown as Coach D gives four graduating vets a chance to choreograph a trio, and the winner's routine will represent the team in a national competition. The heat rises in the studio as the senior Dollhouse residents all clamor for one coveted spot. Meanwhile, the boys struggle to keep their heads above water.

episodes.name: Survival of the Fittest
episodes.overview: Coach D prepares the team for a huge survivor-style elimination match, where heavy hitters can be picked off by the opposing teams; Jaylene battles personal demons that affect her performance; one of the vets suffers a debilitating injury.

episodes.name: A Boy, a Kiss, and a Choreographer
episodes.overview: Coach D breaks the team into pairs of two, with the winning duo getting the opportunity to represent the Dancing Dolls at an elite competition; Coach D enlists celebrity choreographer Don Draico to train the boys from the ground up.

episodes.name: A Star Is Born
episodes.overview: The ALDC heads to Australia to perform at the ASTRA Awards; Abby loses her passport and leaves the team stranded in Sydney without her; Jess confronts the other mothers; Maddie misses a crucial rehearsal when she goes to an interview in Abby's place.

episodes.name: Breaking the Curse of the B-Squad
episodes.overview: The B-Squad prepares for an epic Stand Battle including participation from the DDP and the boys; the Dollhouse quickly becomes a madhouse as the DDP fails to impress, the boys struggle with stands, and the B-Squad suffers from lack of confidence.

episodes.name: Dancing Doll Heist
episodes.overview: While Coach D prepares the most heavy-hitting dancers for an elite national tour during hell week, Coach Marquell trains the new crop of Dolls for their first competition ever, alongside the B-squad, boys and babies.

episodes.name: The Seniors' Last Battle
episodes.overview: It's the final competition of the majorette season, and the team wants to send the Doll seniors off with a final win before they head out on the national tour; newbies can't seem to get a complicated Barbie-inspired routine to not look plastic.

episodes.name: Bring It Live! Detour
episodes.overview: The Dancing Dolls hit the road, but obstacles along the way leave the fate of the tour in jeopardy; Princess battles overcoming her fears; Kayla tries to find her voice through dance; Faith struggles to find confidence on the floor after an injury.
